               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18000917-55-person593">
                  JAMES 
                  SILSOE
               <interp inst="t18000917-55-person593" type="surname" value="SILSOE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-55-person593" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-55-person593" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am chamberlain to Mr. Brewer: On the 22d of July, the prisoner came in about twelve o'clock at night, and asked for a bed; I lighted him to bed, and he paid me for it, one shilling and sixpence; when he was gone, we missed the curtains; there had been nobody in the room besides myself, it was a double bedded room; there was one curtain gone from each bed; I saw them again on the 25th, at Guildhall.</p>
